Q. to
William Dunn
) Do you know the Prisoner at the Bar?

Q. (to
Terence King
) What have you to say against the Prisoner?

Q. (to
William Barker
) What do you know of this Matter?

Q. (to
Sarah Bell
) What have you to say against the Prisoner?

Q. (to
Rachel Beckerly
) What have you to say to the Prisoner?

Q. (to
William Marshall
) What have you to say against the Prisoner at the Bar?

Denker. In less than eight Minutes time; that Woman (
Eleanor Morral
) declar'd upon her Oath she saw that Man (the Prisoner) take it out of my Pocket.

The Woman (
Eleanor Morral
) desir'd the Pawnbroker might be ask'd if the Prisoner (
John Pagon
) had brought no Watches there to pawn.

Hallum. I was not in Bed, but upon the Bed. When I awoke in the Morning, I put my Hand in my Pocket to find my Watch; I found it was gone; she (
Sarah Fox
) said my Watch was above Stairs: I desir'd she would call her Mistress down Stairs; when her Mistress came down, I ask'd her for my Watch; she told me she knew nothing of my Watch, and said to me you, saucy Rascal, how would you like to be nab'd?
